The paper proposes a framework based on deep convolutional neural networks for automatic heart sound classification. This involves designing a 1D-CNN and a 2D-CNN, as well as a time-frequency CNN ensemble. The paper focuses on machine learning and signal processing techniques for classification, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
